A 42-year-old woman, Temitope Akinola, a resident of Isote area of Shagamu, was on Thursday arrested by operatives of the Ogun State Police Command for allegedly poisoning her two-day-old grand-daughter to death with sniper insecticide. Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) Abimbola Oyeyemi, the Police Public Relations Officer of Ogun State Police Command, told DAILY INDEPENDENT  Sunday that her arrest followed information received by police in Shagamu division after the reported death of the child. It was gathered that the suspect, who had never hidden her hatred for her son-in-law who happened to be the father of the baby was the only person with the child while the baby’s mother went to take her bath, only for her to return and met the lifeless body of the baby. Oyeyemi said upon the information gathered, the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) Shagamu Division Superintendent of Police (SP) Okiki Agunbiade detailed his detectives to the scene where the alleged killer grandmother was promptly arrested. The police said on interrogation, the suspect admitted killing the baby because she didn’t like her daughter getting married to the father of the deceased baby. “She confessed further that when she discovered that her daughter was pregnant, she made an attempt to terminate the pregnancy but her pastor warned her not to do so hence she waited for her to deliver before carrying out her devilish intention. “She explained further that she poisoned the baby with a deadly insecticide known as sniper. “Corpse of the baby has been deposited at Olabisi Onabanjo Teaching Hospital mortuary for autopsy, while the suspect has been transferred to the homicide section of the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department (SCIID) for further investigation and prosecution,” Oyeyemi explained.